"User composite-cone posted: "User composite-cone posted: 

@moderator, I'm just saying, if we're all about fostering a knowledge-building community, shouldn't we be allowing for diverse opinions and healthy debates? I mean, isn't that how we learn and grow? Or are we just here to echo each other's thoughts and never challenge the status quo? Just a thought..."

@windy-swale, I get what you're saying, but isn't it a bit hypocritical to ask for respectful discussions while also asking people to adjust their tone? I mean, isn't that a form of censorship? Just food for thought..."

@salty-align, I'm not trying to pick a fight, but I can't help but notice that you seem to be a bit... intense. Maybe you should take a break and come back when you're feeling a bit calmer. Just a friendly suggestion..."

@future-acacia, I'm not sure if you're aware, but your support for the moderator's decisions is a bit... predictable. Don't you think it's time to start questioning authority and thinking for yourself? Just a thought..."

#NotMyModerator"

